Subject: [PATCH 43/44] =?UTF-8?q?inline-3d(#18):=20XRDisplayLayer.excludeE?=
 =?UTF-8?q?lement=20=E2=80=94=20declare=202D=20overlays=20over=20a=20woven?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20element?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The web-facing half of overlay exclusion (displayxr-browser#18). A page marks a
2D DOM element painted over a woven inline-3D canvas (a hover plate, badge) so
the browser composites it as crisp 2D over the woven 3D instead of weaving it.

- excludeElement(el, {composite}) / unexcludeElement(el) on XRDisplayLayer;
  XRDisplayLayerExclusionInit + Composite enum ("over" in v1; "under" reserved,
  throws NotSupportedError). excluded_elements_ cleared on close().
- XRSession::ReportInline3DRects reports each excluded element's rect alongside
  the canvas rects (one atomic push); FrameWidget / WebFrameWidgetImpl carry
  both vectors together.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
